  "elapsed_s": 8.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Shall I pick it up?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "This song was a song about the people who worked on the airport, and it prescribed the ingenuity how to survive.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Wherever they used to stop, they tried to buy a potato, a piece of bread, or to change their clothing, or their own belongings for something else.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It's a sad story.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It's a sad song.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Many people died on this aerodrome, which is airport.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It was only a military airport, which was built or rebuilt by the Russian army in 1940, and it served the Northern Front, Russia.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They used to come, the big planes.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "The [NON-ENGLISH], what flies around here in South Africa, was one of them.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Three-engine planes, this was the biggest those days.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And this song [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] is two meanings.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "One, when they say, when  it sits on this track, and it stops, wherever it stops, it tried to buy food and to exchange clothing, maybe money too, if there was some money.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And-- and the other meaning was, if you belong to this brigade, and in a special brigade, you're lucky, you can survive sometimes.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Because if you haven't got a job altogether, you don't stay a chance to surviving together.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And many people lost their lives by beating them.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "When the Jewish women started to work there first on the airport, there were Russian prisoners who worked.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And they used to come back and say stories that the Germans, the SS and even the Wehrmacht, used to chop off the Russian soldier's head for no reason at all, because it was a prisoner of war.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And the work was very hard and very dangerous.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "First of all, they dealed with explosive things, with bombs or other stuff.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
